content.description: Balency delicate climbing, not very long but worthy !
content.protection: Micro to med
content.location: Thin seam right of Distant Vision. Use Dirty Dancing anchor.

content.description: Good route to start on in this zone of the canyon.
content.protection: Small to Large
content.location: 100ft right of concrete gully.

content.description: Follow the crack up the challenging start to easier climbing above. After 2/3 of the way up, move left into the anchors. This route shares its anchors with its neighbor climb ('Left of Slipstream 10a) to the left.
content.protection: Trad to two bolted anchors. Small to medium pro
content.location: The second route to the left of the bolted cave route (Bohemian 11c).

content.description: Great beginner lead!
content.protection: Small to Medium
content.location: Second route left of "Concrete Gully".

content.description: Kind of a spicy lead!
content.protection: Micro to Medium, long runners nice!
content.location: Climbs arÃªte between Disco Inferno and Finger Licking Good finishing on F.L.G. anchor.

content.description: Fun face climbing over small gear!
content.protection: Micro to Medium, TCU's nice
content.location: Starts on Dirty Dog Ditty, once you reach the ramp head left to a thin crack. Stay left , has its own anchor !

content.description: Steep crack right of "Bohemian".
content.protection: Small to Medium
content.location: Start on the right side of the cave.

content.description: Way fun start on the seam to the left of the crack that makes 'Slipstream'. Move right after the start and stay on the arete as long as you can. This route shares its anchors with its neighbor climb ('Slipstream 5.9) to the right.
content.protection: Top Rope (use two bolted anchors from Slipstream)
content.location: Self explanatory... but it's the route to the left of Slipstream.

content.description: Start under a small roof to the left of Distant Vision.  Climb to the right of the roof to a drilled piton, then up to a small ledge.  A yellow alien or comparable sized piece is required to fit into a small pocket which protects moderate face moves up to a crack.  Follow the crack then pull out a small bulge to the right and the anchors.
content.protection: Single set of nuts/cams including a mandatory yellow alien/TCU.
content.location: To the left of Concrete Gully, directly left of Distant Vision.

content.description: Start up some pockets to a nice crack that pulls through the roof.
content.protection: Small to Medium pro. Bolted anchor
content.location: A few routes downstream from the concrete jungle descent gully. First route right of Liberty Bell.

content.description: Bad rock to locks, follow the crack left
content.protection: Small to medium
content.location: Climber's left of the classic past 6 routes to the left end of the chossy cave, right around corner from disco inferno

content.description: Thin but protectable moves down low lead up to a great rest and a second little crux at the beginning of a rattly finger crack.  Stem the flake out right for maximum aid or climb the crack straight on for maximum challenge.
content.protection: Small stoppers and finger sized cams.  One or two small hand cams helpful up top.  Two bolt anchor.
content.location: Climb starts to the left of Concrete Gulley.  Obvious thin crack up to a small ledge where more obvious finger to hand crack starts.

content.description: The aesthetic crack facing up canyon! Classic of the area!
content.protection: Micro to Medium TCU's
content.location: Just right of "Dirty Dog Ditty" OW!

content.description: Climb hands to ODub/fingers double crack, back to hands.  It is a super fun & varied little pitch.
content.protection: Doubles yellow to purple Metolius, or lose the blues and bring one big cam.  You can protect the OW with the finger crack.
content.location: This is left of Disco Inferno, right of Magic Carpet Ride, climber's right of the Concrete Gully.

content.description: Start up Sidewalk, and pas through the roof on the left hand side.
content.protection: Fixed anchors.  Gear can be challenging to place.
content.location: Same start as Sidewalk.

content.description:
Start off with easy left leaning hand crack up to ledge. Then continue up corner. Climb becomes over hanging (crux) in the middle of the upper half.  

  Two old bolted chains on top.
content.protection: Multiple medium to large. There is a great .5 placement in the upper half.
content.location: Right of Heal Scum 11a and right of Matt's Arete 12a.

content.description: A couple of thin moves lead to one hard move pulling into the upper section of this short climb.
content.protection: Medium and small gear. Two rap bolts at the top.
content.location: First route upstream from the concrete jungle descent gully.

content.description: Fun mixed route. Superb cranking if you can fight off the pump to reach the anchors.
content.protection: 4 bolts #1,1.5,2 friend
content.location: Left of concrete gully.

content.description: Steep start.
content.protection: Small to Large
content.location: Just left of the Bohemian Cave.

content.description: Climbing is rather engaging up high!
content.protection: Small to Medium
content.location: 2nd crack right of cave , a little chossy to start!

content.description: This zone is primarily west of Concrete Jungle Gully. All routes after "Cellulose" are east of the gully. The area's east of C. G. is Civil Suit, then the Remainder area starting with "Split Pea".
